          <p>Geometry Dash was created by developer Robert Topala (known as RobTop) and released in 2013 for mobile devices. What started as a small one-button game quickly grew into a global success thanks to its intense gameplay and strong community of players and creators. Over time, new levels, icons, and game modes were added through updates.</p>
          
          <p>The game also introduced a powerful level editor that allowed the community to design and share their own challenges. Many of these player-made levels became as famous as the official ones. The success of Geometry Dash also inspired spin-off versions like <strong><a href="/geometry-dash-lite/">Geometry Dash Lite</a></strong>, <strong><a href="/geometry-dash-meltdown/">Geometry Dash Meltdown</a></strong>, <strong><a href="/geometry-dash-subzero/">Geometry Dash SubZero</a></strong>, and <strong><a href="/geometry-dash-breeze/">Geometry Dash Breeze</a></strong>. Each one adds new music, levels, and visual themes to the main formula.</p>
          
